WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.359
Hey, where is my 72-year-old couple?

00:00:03.359 --> 00:00:04.559
They're not here tonight.

00:00:04.559 --> 00:00:06.599
Amen.

00:00:06.599 --> 00:00:09.000
When you said that, it gave me a sweet memory.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:11.920
I'm old enough, and some of you are as well,

00:00:11.920 --> 00:00:16.559
to remember when Paul Harvey was daily on the radio.

00:00:16.559 --> 00:00:19.440
And I used to really enjoy listening to him.

00:00:19.440 --> 00:00:22.879
And once a week, or maybe a couple times a week,

00:00:22.879 --> 00:00:26.959
he had what he called the Tournament of Roses.

00:00:26.959 --> 00:00:30.479
And he would announce a couple, maybe,

00:00:30.479 --> 00:00:33.919
it seemed to me they were always from the Midwest or the Heartland

00:00:33.919 --> 00:00:38.159
somewhere, that had been married for 70 or more years.

00:00:38.159 --> 00:00:40.799
And I think, on Paul Harvey's show,

00:00:40.799 --> 00:00:45.360
I think the longest I heard was 72 years.

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:47.959
But then I was sitting in Charlotte,

00:00:47.959 --> 00:00:51.520
it's been two years ago, listening to the local news

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.479
trying to catch the weather.

00:00:53.479 --> 00:00:57.319
And they brought on an interest of local interest.

00:00:57.319 --> 00:01:02.919
And they were celebrating Dewey and D.B. Williams.

00:01:02.919 --> 00:01:07.559
And they had been married 82 years, both of them

00:01:07.559 --> 00:01:09.879
over 100 years old.

00:01:09.879 --> 00:01:11.879
And they asked Dewey, they said, what

00:01:11.879 --> 00:01:16.959
is the secret for a marriage that lasts 82 years?

00:01:16.959 --> 00:01:18.639
And he was a godly fellow.

00:01:18.639 --> 00:01:22.639
And he said, keep Christ in the middle

00:01:22.639 --> 00:01:25.559
and do what she says.

00:01:25.559 --> 00:01:28.519
I thought, that's pretty close to just what it takes.

00:01:28.519 --> 00:01:30.360
Amen.

00:01:30.360 --> 00:01:31.120
Amen.

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:32.559
Well, it's good to be here tonight.

00:01:32.559 --> 00:01:34.239
And I trust you had a great day.

00:01:34.239 --> 00:01:36.080
It's been a beautiful day.

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:40.440
And now let's see what the Lord has to say for us, or say to us.

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:44.319
I invite you to turn to Psalm 66.

00:01:44.319 --> 00:01:54.639
Psalm 66, a familiar couple of verses,

00:01:54.639 --> 00:01:59.160
I think essential for our thinking tonight.

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:02.839
Psalm 66, and let's just read starting with verse 18.

00:02:02.839 --> 00:02:14.320
The Bible says, if I regard iniquity in my heart,

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:17.520
the Lord will not hear me.

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:21.639
But verily God hath heard me.

00:02:21.639 --> 00:02:24.600
He hath attended to the voice of my prayer.

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:29.639
Blessed be the God which hath not turned away my prayer,

00:02:29.639 --> 00:02:33.119
nor his mercy from me.

00:02:33.119 --> 00:02:35.199
Let's pray.

00:02:35.199 --> 00:02:37.720
Father, I thank you for the day you've

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:38.839
given us, the beauty of it.

00:02:38.839 --> 00:02:41.639
Thank you for this good group of people,

00:02:41.639 --> 00:02:45.479
the sweetness of this fellowship.

00:02:45.479 --> 00:02:49.559
Lord, we come before you tonight confessing our need of you

00:02:49.559 --> 00:02:52.479
to speak to us.

00:02:52.479 --> 00:02:58.199
Lord, I pray that your Holy Spirit would minister to us.

00:02:58.199 --> 00:03:00.800
I pray that none would be offended,

00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:04.960
that all would take these moments as a time

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:06.559
to look into our own hearts.

00:03:09.160 --> 00:03:11.839
Father, would you use this time, and would you

00:03:11.839 --> 00:03:16.399
help us to be more pleasing and fruitful in our walk with thee?

00:03:16.399 --> 00:03:20.240
We pray in Jesus' name, amen.

00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:22.839
I always like to give an introduction

00:03:22.839 --> 00:03:25.679
to my introduction when I preach this message.

00:03:25.679 --> 00:03:27.839
I haven't preached it a lot, because I can't

00:03:27.839 --> 00:03:29.960
preach it everywhere I go.

00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:34.240
But I will preach it to you tonight.

00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:37.320
I know who I'm speaking to tonight.

00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:42.240
I'm speaking to the cream of the crop of Fellowship Baptist

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:43.440
Church.

00:03:43.440 --> 00:03:46.720
I'm preaching to people that will come out

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:51.279
on a Sunday evening because they want to hear the word of God,

00:03:51.279 --> 00:03:55.600
and because they want God to do something in their hearts

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:58.080
and with their lives.

00:03:58.080 --> 00:04:02.119
So if at any time tonight I sound as if I'm scolding,

00:04:02.119 --> 00:04:03.919
I'm not scolding.

00:04:03.919 --> 00:04:06.240
I'm not at all trying to be harsh.

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:10.919
I just know that we are sincere about our desire

00:04:10.919 --> 00:04:15.320
to be what God wants us to be.

00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:19.160
We so often talk about revival.

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:21.920
Matter of fact, sometimes we talk so much about revival

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:26.480
that in some ways it loses its meaning.

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:29.440
I don't mean to be critical of what anyone else does

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:31.079
or whatever else happens.

00:04:31.079 --> 00:04:34.679
But I, from time to time, hear about a revival

00:04:34.679 --> 00:04:36.480
on a college campus.

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:39.079
And I hope there is revival on college campuses.

00:04:39.079 --> 00:04:41.880
But it tends to be when I look into what they're

00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:46.799
talking about, they're talking about people being baptized

00:04:46.799 --> 00:04:50.519
but by people who don't have authority to baptize

00:04:50.519 --> 00:04:53.000
and calling baptism revival.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:55.160
And what maybe they're responding to

00:04:55.160 --> 00:05:00.320
is the emotionalism of some kind of concert or emotionalism

00:05:00.320 --> 00:05:02.440
to a crisis of the moment.

00:05:02.440 --> 00:05:04.000
And I'm not, again, please don't hear

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.160
me trying to be hypercritical.

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:10.600
I'm just saying that we use the term revival so much

00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:15.480
that sometimes we just make it into an emotional thing

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:20.359
when there's not much that lives past the moment, the day,

00:05:20.359 --> 00:05:22.480
or the week.

00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:25.760
Every revival that I have ever heard of

00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:29.239
or have personally experienced, you say, preacher,

00:05:29.239 --> 00:05:30.559
have you experienced revival?

00:05:30.559 --> 00:05:32.640
Yes, I have.

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:35.720
But every revival that I have heard of that I think

00:05:35.720 --> 00:05:38.440
is legitimate and that I have experienced

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:40.480
starts with prayer.

00:05:43.519 --> 00:05:50.000
I don't see revivals that start in halls with great crowds.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:54.959
I see that as where revivals go.

00:05:54.959 --> 00:06:02.160
Revivals start when people, from their own heart

00:06:02.160 --> 00:06:07.040
and their own need, get right with God

00:06:07.040 --> 00:06:11.600
and are on praying ground and begin to ask

00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:16.720
God to work in their hearts.

00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:18.880
I've been a pastor for a long time,

00:06:18.880 --> 00:06:22.519
and I've preached on prayer many, many times

00:06:22.519 --> 00:06:27.880
and tried to help people develop a plan of praying.

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:32.239
And all the things that that entails, I keep a prayer

00:06:32.239 --> 00:06:36.359
journal, and I journal much of what I ask God for

00:06:36.359 --> 00:06:38.480
and much of what God says to me.

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:44.480
And I say to him, I think it's good to have a plan of prayer.

00:06:44.480 --> 00:06:49.000
I try to pray every day at a certain time

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:54.799
in a certain program, because I need to be lashed to that.

00:06:54.799 --> 00:07:01.000
I am a man who, I think I was born with ADHD, whatever it is.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:04.799
And I have to lash myself to a program.

00:07:04.799 --> 00:07:08.519
I have to make myself be there, and otherwise my mind

00:07:08.519 --> 00:07:10.320
wanders and so on.

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:12.359
You say, what are you saying all this for?

00:07:12.359 --> 00:07:18.959
Well, as important as the plan is, and it is important,

00:07:18.959 --> 00:07:22.200
it is not the most important thing.

00:07:22.200 --> 00:07:25.480
We can have the greatest journal and the greatest plan

00:07:25.480 --> 00:07:26.679
for praying.

00:07:26.679 --> 00:07:30.000
We can lash ourselves to a discipline of a schedule

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:31.640
and go there and pray.

00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:33.559
But I'm telling you, if we get there

00:07:33.559 --> 00:07:39.160
with a heart that has something in it that

00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:46.679
blocks God from hearing, then all of our plan

00:07:46.679 --> 00:07:50.359
and all of our discipline are simply a way

00:07:50.359 --> 00:07:53.679
that we can check a personal box that says,

00:07:53.679 --> 00:07:56.959
look how good you did.

00:07:56.959 --> 00:07:59.839
And I think if we were honest, when it all comes down

00:07:59.839 --> 00:08:05.160
to it, what actually we need to focus on as believers who

00:08:05.160 --> 00:08:07.880
do love the Lord, who are here because we

00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:11.720
want to serve the Lord, is we maybe for a while

00:08:11.720 --> 00:08:14.959
need to stop seeing the wrong in the world.

00:08:14.959 --> 00:08:17.799
And man, is there a lot to see.

00:08:17.799 --> 00:08:22.000
And stop examining everyone else's heart and motive

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:28.160
and life, and maybe just say, what about my heart?

00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:33.520
Is there something limiting in my heart?

00:08:33.520 --> 00:08:35.719
I think it's important to understand

00:08:35.719 --> 00:08:38.960
that when God says, if someone regards an iniquity,

00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:41.520
he will not hear me.

00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:43.159
I want you to understand that word here.

00:08:43.159 --> 00:08:46.479
It's an important Hebrew word.

00:08:46.479 --> 00:08:49.840
I'm not trying to impress by knowing a Hebrew word.

00:08:49.840 --> 00:08:55.119
I'm trying to get across to you, it is the word shama.

00:08:55.119 --> 00:08:59.159
And the Hebrew had a very different understanding

00:08:59.159 --> 00:09:03.000
of what it was to hear than we necessarily

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:04.359
in our culture today.

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:07.719
We concentrate on the audible hearing,

00:09:07.719 --> 00:09:11.520
and then we'll discern if we want to do what we heard.

00:09:11.520 --> 00:09:15.760
But the Hebrew knew that in your relationship with God,

00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:18.880
you didn't listen and then decide.

00:09:18.880 --> 00:09:23.599
You listened with the intention of doing what God said.

00:09:23.599 --> 00:09:25.640
And God is reversing it now.

00:09:25.640 --> 00:09:29.359
And he is saying, I will hear you.

00:09:29.359 --> 00:09:32.679
But if there is sin, if there's iniquity

00:09:32.719 --> 00:09:35.000
that you're regarding in your heart,

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:38.599
I won't be moved by your prayer.

00:09:38.599 --> 00:09:40.159
Someone says, does God hear me?

00:09:40.159 --> 00:09:42.119
Yeah, God hears you.

00:09:42.119 --> 00:09:47.239
But God may not be inclined to answer in that way

00:09:47.239 --> 00:09:51.239
or in that moment because we have regarded

00:09:51.239 --> 00:09:54.280
iniquity in our heart.

00:09:54.280 --> 00:09:59.039
The surest way to a powerless prayer life

00:09:59.039 --> 00:10:01.080
is to regard iniquity.

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:08.720
iniquity in our heart. John Bunyan, who was the author of Pilgrim's Progress, he was a

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:15.320
writer and journaler, he wrote this in his journal one time, prayer is a shield to the

00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:25.320
soul, a sacrifice to God, and a scourge to Satan. True statement. Sometime after that,

00:10:25.320 --> 00:10:30.200
a matter of weeks after that, he came back to his journal and he added this line to that

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:42.880
one, prayer will make a man cease from sin, but sin will make a man cease from prayer.

00:10:42.880 --> 00:10:50.120
I wonder if our prayer lives are anemic, not because we don't have a plan, not because

00:10:50.120 --> 00:10:58.040
we lack knowledge of how to pray, not because we don't have discipline to at least fulfill

00:10:58.040 --> 00:11:06.200
the function, I wonder if our prayer lives are anemic in many cases because we have a

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:18.480
limiting part in our heart. Consider it. What is it to accept sin, or what is it to regard

00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:26.560
iniquity in my heart? Let me say this at the outset. There will never be a day when I bow

00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:36.680
my knee before the Lord and pray that I will not have sin in my heart. Okay? I'm not trying to

00:11:36.680 --> 00:11:43.920
confess my sin to you, I'm not trying to make, I'm not trying to be humble publicly, I'm just

00:11:43.920 --> 00:11:52.000
telling you the truth. I'm a sinner. And since I've been saved, I still am a sinner. And the

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:58.840
reason I feel okay telling you that is because I know you. And whether you would ever want to

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:05.800
admit it, you're a sinner like I'm a sinner. There is never a day when I don't wait and say,

00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:15.160
God, I think I can pray today because I've been really good. On my best day, I don't deserve to

00:12:15.160 --> 00:12:22.320
go before God. And on my worst day, I don't deserve to go before God. I'm not saying to you,

00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:30.280
if you're a sinner and you somehow have not come to the state of sinless perfection. You know,

00:12:30.280 --> 00:12:35.520
that is a doctrine that our world, some in our world observe, not so many today as before. But

00:12:35.520 --> 00:12:43.200
they thought that you could become so holy that you no longer committed sin in your life in this

00:12:43.360 --> 00:12:49.720
body. Not happening. We will be sinlessly perfect someday when we are in the presence of the Lord in

00:12:49.720 --> 00:12:58.440
heaven. Alright? I'm not saying that if you sin, that you shouldn't even bother to pray. Now,

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:05.480
listen, we are to keep short lists of our sins. We are to confess our sins as we recognize our

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:12.440
sin. We are to have morning times of confession, daily through the day times of confession,

00:13:12.440 --> 00:13:18.280
evening. What I try to do is reflect on how bad I did that day. And before I pillow my head,

00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:26.320
be honest with God and seek His forgiveness. As we see the sin, we are to confess. We are

00:13:26.320 --> 00:13:31.960
to keep short lists of sin. But I'm just telling you, there's been days when I might have forgotten

00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:41.040
one or missed one. Or ten. Or a hundred. I'm not saying don't bother praying unless you're

00:13:41.080 --> 00:13:47.600
sinlessly perfect. None of us would ever be on praying ground. No, no. That's not what God is

00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:55.000
saying. To regard iniquity in my heart is something very different. Then what is it,

00:13:55.000 --> 00:14:06.560
preacher? It is this. It is allowing the sin to stay in my heart. It is seeing it,

00:14:06.800 --> 00:14:18.280
acknowledging its presence, contemplating it, maybe even in some way insincerely noting and

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:27.360
confessing it. But it is not clearing that sin out of my heart. It's not a stumbling into sin.

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:35.280
It's not a mistake I made. It is that I have seen it and I have allowed it to stay in my heart.

00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:43.840
It even has the concept of agreeing with it. When I regard iniquity, I see it. I know it's

00:14:43.840 --> 00:14:51.720
there. I allow it to stay there because somehow, I don't know, I say stuff like this. Well,

00:14:51.720 --> 00:15:01.120
God understands it's just who I am. You have to understand, preacher, my mom was this way.

00:15:01.440 --> 00:15:05.720
My dad was this way. You have to understand, preacher, it's just who I am. I don't mean for

00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:13.760
it to be bad. It's just who I am. We have a new one now. If you've seen the commercials,

00:15:13.760 --> 00:15:20.520
God gets us. That's another way of saying, you're okay. Don't worry about it. God gets me. I know

00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:26.640
I just berated my wife with my temper. I know I just lashed out at her with my tongue, but it's

00:15:26.640 --> 00:15:36.040
who I am. I'll get over it, and I'll tell her I'm sorry, and it'll be okay. But it's not okay.

00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:42.680
Well, it's just, you have to understand, preacher, I was born like this, and man,

00:15:42.680 --> 00:15:48.960
I've been like this for so long. And here's my message to you thus far. Stop being that way.

00:15:48.960 --> 00:16:00.840
God gave us the Holy Spirit to stop being that way. And we will never stop being that way until

00:16:00.840 --> 00:16:09.280
we stop excusing ourselves for being that way. And it's not okay with God that it's how you've

00:16:09.280 --> 00:16:15.760
always been. And it's not okay that you'll get over it in a minute. And it's not okay that it's

00:16:15.760 --> 00:16:22.200
who you are, and everybody just has to understand. No, they don't. And God doesn't understand. And

00:16:22.200 --> 00:16:32.360
it is a serious matter. It's a tragedy when our deceitful hearts convince us that godly living

00:16:32.360 --> 00:16:44.280
is consistent with us approving our sin. And that's a heavy statement. You do remember our

00:16:44.280 --> 00:16:51.240
hearts, don't you? They're deceitfully wicked. They're desperately wicked. And yet we can

00:16:51.240 --> 00:16:56.800
convince our sin, yes, I know that's in there. Yes, I know that I react that way. Yes, I know

00:16:56.800 --> 00:17:02.480
this, that, and the other. But, you know, it's just who I am. And man, I love God, and God's

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:13.440
using me. Stop it. You see, the tragedy is this. The longer sin stays, the more it spoils. It starts

00:17:13.440 --> 00:17:21.960
by spoiling my personal walk with the Lord. Devotions become empty. Prayer becomes dry. I am

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:28.280
convinced that a lot of folks do not feel the necessity or lay out the time for prayer because

00:17:28.280 --> 00:17:36.360
they know that limitation is already in their heart. It begins to affect our church life. It

00:17:36.360 --> 00:17:43.200
makes preaching not as good and not as interesting. Our giving and serving become drudgery, not

00:17:43.200 --> 00:17:50.960
living and exciting. Eventually it works its way into our perspective at home, and everything is

00:17:50.960 --> 00:17:57.120
colored by it. It works its way into our marriage. It works its way into our relationship. We become

00:17:57.120 --> 00:18:03.280
cynical, negative. We excuse ourselves, and thus we have to criticize the world, judge the world.

00:18:03.280 --> 00:18:14.560
No sin can be accepted and approved in a believer's life. What we have become in this

00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:25.040
generation is incredibly good at making it someone else's fault. Yeah, I know I'm the way I am, but

00:18:25.040 --> 00:18:32.920
you have to understand it's not my fault. I love to point out in this verse, notice verse 18 again,

00:18:33.080 --> 00:18:46.720
three words, I'll emphasize them. If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me.

00:18:46.720 --> 00:18:58.239
I, my, me. It is not someone else's fault that you have a limiting quality in your heart. It's not

00:18:58.320 --> 00:19:06.239
what somebody did to you that you have a limiting quality in your heart. Accepting and approving

00:19:06.239 --> 00:19:16.720
sin is not what is done to you. It is what you do to yourself. It's in your heart. Not only is it in

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:28.080
my heart, but because it's in my heart, sometimes I can hide it. Sometimes I can kind of disguise it

00:19:28.080 --> 00:19:35.200
and masquerade it, and I think that somehow I can get away with it because it's down in the deep

00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:44.880
recesses of my heart. I often think of David after he committed that horrible sin with Bathsheba.

00:19:47.360 --> 00:19:54.400
And after he went through the deceitfulness with Uriah, the horrible command to Joab to

00:19:54.400 --> 00:20:00.880
retreat from Uriah at the wall and let him be killed, how he went when that was a

00:20:00.880 --> 00:20:04.880
accomplished and brought Bathsheba into his home, and

00:20:04.880 --> 00:20:08.880
oh, wise and righteous David, sweet singer of Israel,

00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:12.880
marries her. Oh, he did all the things to make

00:20:12.880 --> 00:20:16.880
himself look good, but all the time in his heart

00:20:16.880 --> 00:20:20.880
he knows. He knows.

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:24.880
Oh, he still went to Tabernacle. He still

00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:28.880
led. He still sang his songs. He even wrote some, but if you

00:20:28.880 --> 00:20:32.880
look at the ones that he wrote while he was hiding that sin and

00:20:32.880 --> 00:20:36.880
acting as if it wasn't there, they are painful psalms where

00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:40.880
he talks about rotting from the inside out.

00:20:40.880 --> 00:20:44.880
Now please, don't misunderstand what I'm saying.

00:20:44.880 --> 00:20:48.880
No one here

00:20:48.880 --> 00:20:52.880
is guilty of such horrible sin as David in adultery,

00:20:52.880 --> 00:20:56.880
murder, and so the like.

00:20:56.880 --> 00:21:00.880
But as David was willing to try

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:04.880
to cover it, so are we sometimes trying to cover it,

00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:08.880
willing to try and cover it. And we're so willing for it to be

00:21:08.880 --> 00:21:12.880
what somebody else did to us. Well, you have to understand, preacher, I

00:21:12.880 --> 00:21:16.880
wouldn't be like this but my dad. I wouldn't be like this but

00:21:16.880 --> 00:21:20.880
my youth pastor. I wouldn't be like this but my wife. And we can go

00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:24.880
on and on and on, but when God says it,

00:21:24.880 --> 00:21:28.880
when he says it's your heart, it's your iniquity,

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:32.880
it's your limited prayer life, stop making it

00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:36.880
everybody else and stop trying to act

00:21:36.880 --> 00:21:40.880
like it's not there. And stop trying to act

00:21:40.880 --> 00:21:44.880
like we can lead godly, powerful lives

00:21:44.880 --> 00:21:48.880
for the Lord when we know it's there.

00:21:48.880 --> 00:21:52.880
What's the result?

00:21:52.880 --> 00:21:56.880
Well, the consequences are very simple.

00:21:56.880 --> 00:22:00.880
God is unmoved.

00:22:00.880 --> 00:22:04.880
God, when we pray, is unmoved.

00:22:04.880 --> 00:22:08.880
God wants to work on our behalf. He wants to

00:22:08.880 --> 00:22:12.880
show himself mighty for us. However, when we approve

00:22:12.880 --> 00:22:16.880
of sin in our hearts and we disapprove of God,

00:22:16.880 --> 00:22:20.880
God will not work in the way that we ask because it would

00:22:20.880 --> 00:22:24.880
be him approving of our sin.

00:22:24.880 --> 00:22:28.880
I hope that's easy to see.

00:22:28.880 --> 00:22:32.880
Prayer is unheard. The Lord will not hear me. When I go and I pray

00:22:32.880 --> 00:22:36.880
for my child, as desperate as

00:22:36.880 --> 00:22:40.880
I am and as great as the crisis might be,

00:22:40.880 --> 00:22:44.880
my limiting heart may keep God

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:48.880
from working. When I pray

00:22:48.880 --> 00:22:52.880
for my ministry, when I pray for my health, when I pray for my job,

00:22:52.880 --> 00:22:56.880
man, I don't want to have in the back of my mind, boy,

00:22:56.880 --> 00:23:00.880
I really need God to work, but man, I've got this.

00:23:00.880 --> 00:23:04.880
That's why we don't pray. That's why we don't

00:23:04.880 --> 00:23:08.880
see the answers because we know before we say, oh God,

00:23:08.880 --> 00:23:12.880
we know we've kept it right where

00:23:12.880 --> 00:23:16.880
we can find it.

00:23:16.880 --> 00:23:20.880
Say, preacher, we don't like you tonight.

00:23:20.880 --> 00:23:24.880
We liked you a little this morning. We don't

00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:28.880
like you tonight. Well, you don't have to do

00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:32.880
any of this, but please stop talking about

00:23:32.880 --> 00:23:36.880
revival.

00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:40.880
Please stop acting as if

00:23:40.880 --> 00:23:44.880
we can make God over into our image and we can tell

00:23:44.880 --> 00:23:48.880
God what He should accept about us and we can tell God how He should

00:23:48.880 --> 00:23:52.880
leave us and we can tell God what we will allow Him to mess with and what we won't

00:23:52.880 --> 00:23:56.880
allow Him to mess with.

00:23:56.880 --> 00:24:00.880
Because when we regard iniquity,

00:24:00.880 --> 00:24:04.880
when we accept it as who we are and

00:24:04.880 --> 00:24:08.880
we're satisfied, God says I'm unmoved.

00:24:08.880 --> 00:24:12.880
What are you talking about, preacher?

00:24:12.880 --> 00:24:16.880
Are you accusing us of being wicked, horrible people?

00:24:16.880 --> 00:24:20.880
No, I'm not. But I am saying this,

00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:24.880
that a little leaven leaveneth the whole lump.

00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:28.880
And whether we like to accept

00:24:28.880 --> 00:24:32.880
that as true, oh, we know it's a spiritual principle and it's true

00:24:32.880 --> 00:24:36.880
in everyone else's life, but it's not, God understands,

00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:40.880
not true in my life. That little thing where I

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:44.880
hold on to it and it limits God, well, it's just not true in my, yes, it is true

00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:48.880
in your life. A little leaven does

00:24:48.880 --> 00:24:52.880
change your entire life.

00:24:52.880 --> 00:24:56.880
I am told

00:24:56.880 --> 00:25:00.880
that cancer starts as one single

00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:04.880
cell. I am not a scientist. I don't know if that's true,

00:25:04.880 --> 00:25:08.880
but I'm preaching, so stay out of my message.

00:25:08.880 --> 00:25:12.880
One single cell. And what if we had

00:25:12.880 --> 00:25:16.880
such great technology that with a simple test

00:25:16.880 --> 00:25:20.880
you could discern you have that one single cell.

00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:24.880
We did a scan. We know where it is. We can get that

00:25:24.880 --> 00:25:28.880
out before it divides and multiplies. Let us get that

00:25:28.880 --> 00:25:32.880
out. And our answer would be,

00:25:32.880 --> 00:25:36.880
it's just who I am.

00:25:36.880 --> 00:25:40.880
God understands. It's just who I am.

00:25:40.880 --> 00:25:44.880
Not one of us would say that.

00:25:44.880 --> 00:25:48.880
We would say, today, get it out of me.

00:25:48.880 --> 00:25:52.880
Because we know the debilitating effect

00:25:52.880 --> 00:25:56.880
of that one cell. We know it starts small.

00:25:56.880 --> 00:26:00.880
We know we could deal with it today. We probably could deal with it next year.

00:26:00.880 --> 00:26:04.880
We know that in five years we might be noticing symptoms, but

00:26:04.880 --> 00:26:08.880
maybe not. But if we knew it was there, and we knew

00:26:08.880 --> 00:26:12.880
the course it would take, that it would leaven the whole

00:26:12.880 --> 00:26:16.880
lump, we would say, get

00:26:16.880 --> 00:26:20.880
it out of me now.

00:26:20.880 --> 00:26:24.880
But we are so casual

00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:28.880
about sin, what God

00:26:28.880 --> 00:26:32.880
calls sin, that we

00:26:32.880 --> 00:26:36.880
feel entitled to hold onto it.

00:26:36.880 --> 00:26:40.880
Or we feel powerless to get rid of it.

00:26:40.880 --> 00:26:44.880
Or we've grown comfortable

00:26:44.880 --> 00:26:48.880
with having it. And God says, listen,

00:26:48.880 --> 00:26:52.880
I will forgive sin. I will

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:56.880
forgive sinners. I will change you and grow you

00:26:56.880 --> 00:27:00.880
and help you. But if you purposely

00:27:00.880 --> 00:27:04.880
hold onto your sin,

00:27:04.880 --> 00:27:08.880
you've limited anything I can do in your life.

00:27:08.880 --> 00:27:12.880
You say, preacher, what are you talking about?

00:27:12.880 --> 00:27:16.880
I'm talking about people who have held

00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:20.880
a grudge for 20,

00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:24.880
30, 40 years. I'll never forget

00:27:24.880 --> 00:27:28.880
my wife and I were visiting in the intensive care unit. We were out talking

00:27:28.880 --> 00:27:32.880
to a wife. Her husband was in ICU. They were doing something so we couldn't be in there

00:27:32.880 --> 00:27:36.880
at that moment. She started telling us about something that

00:27:36.880 --> 00:27:40.880
had happened. And boy, I mean, she was getting just really

00:27:40.880 --> 00:27:44.880
upset about it. And her face was getting red. And it was

00:27:44.880 --> 00:27:48.880
something that she was wronged. I mean, somebody

00:27:48.880 --> 00:27:52.880
legitimately did something wrong. And as a pastor, I'm thinking, man, I've got to correct

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:56.880
that. And I said, when did that happen?

00:27:56.880 --> 00:28:00.880
And her answer to me was 40 years

00:28:00.880 --> 00:28:04.880
ago.

00:28:04.880 --> 00:28:08.880
And there are people that feel justified in holding onto

00:28:08.880 --> 00:28:12.880
that hurt. There are people who feel

00:28:12.880 --> 00:28:16.880
justified holding onto that hate.

00:28:16.880 --> 00:28:20.880
And they feel justified because it was done to them.

00:28:20.880 --> 00:28:24.880
And they didn't lash out, but it was done to them. And they may not have reacted

00:28:24.880 --> 00:28:28.880
to it at that moment, but they've held it until it has now

00:28:28.880 --> 00:28:32.880
gone down into their very being, a root of bitterness.

00:28:32.880 --> 00:28:36.880
And they carry it with them. And please don't tell me

00:28:36.880 --> 00:28:40.880
it doesn't mean anything. It colors every perspective

00:28:40.880 --> 00:28:44.880
they have.

00:28:44.880 --> 00:28:48.880
But it's just who they are. Stop it.

00:28:48.880 --> 00:28:52.880
There are people in this room

00:28:52.880 --> 00:28:56.880
who have anger issues,

00:28:56.880 --> 00:29:00.880
temper issues. They lash out

00:29:00.880 --> 00:29:04.880
on the road. They come in the house

00:29:04.880 --> 00:29:08.880
and lash out in the house. They lash out at people they work with.

00:29:08.880 --> 00:29:12.880
They damage their relationship with their spouse. They damage their

00:29:12.880 --> 00:29:16.880
relationship with their children. They're aggravated at everybody at church.

00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:20.880
They say things they're sometimes keeping it a little more Christian.

00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:24.880
They feel justified because they get over it.

00:29:24.880 --> 00:29:28.880
But what they have done in the doing of that

00:29:28.880 --> 00:29:32.880
anger and that temper is destroyed part of a

00:29:32.880 --> 00:29:36.880
relationship. And then their expectation is that everybody should just

00:29:36.880 --> 00:29:40.880
get over it. You don't have a right to be that angry.

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:44.880
You don't have a right to have that kind of temper.

00:29:44.880 --> 00:29:48.880
You don't have a right to say those things

00:29:48.880 --> 00:29:52.880
to people you love. And you don't have a right to excuse yourself

00:29:52.880 --> 00:29:56.880
because your dad was like that or excuse yourself because of

00:29:56.880 --> 00:30:00.880
what somebody did to you first. You don't have the right to hold on

00:30:00.880 --> 00:30:02.880
to that.

00:30:02.880 --> 00:30:14.260
that you are God's child, and when you excuse yourself, God says you've got to deal with it.

00:30:14.260 --> 00:30:29.300
More so men, but becoming more so women. We live in a lustful generation. There are men that can't

00:30:29.300 --> 00:30:38.840
live a day without being consumed with lust. Yeah, preacher, you gotta understand, I'm a man. Yeah,

00:30:38.840 --> 00:30:48.220
you're God's man. And it's not okay. It's not okay to be consumed with that. And listen,

00:30:48.220 --> 00:30:55.340
if you think it is consistent to be consumed with lust and live a godly life as a husband,

00:30:55.340 --> 00:31:05.180
as a church member, as a servant of God, they don't coexist. Stop excusing it. Stop holding

00:31:05.180 --> 00:31:15.060
on to it. You say I've tried. Try again to get rid of it. Get help. But we so limit what God

00:31:15.060 --> 00:31:22.140
can do with us. We so limit how we can speak to God, and God can speak to us when we hold those

00:31:22.300 --> 00:31:30.420
things, and we know they're there. Oh, we're still marching off with our psalms. We're still at

00:31:30.420 --> 00:31:41.180
church. We're still teaching our class. We know it's there, and I can go on for hours. Jealousy,

00:31:41.180 --> 00:31:50.660
envy, people eaten up with the lack of contentment with what God has done in their life. They go to

00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:57.020
church and see somebody else blessed. Somebody else gets to sing the solo they don't get to.

00:31:57.020 --> 00:32:03.660
Somebody else is appreciated. I've literally had people say, Pastor, you shook so-and-so's hand.

00:32:03.660 --> 00:32:16.779
You never shook my hand. That's the reason. No, I would never say that. Stop it. That's

00:32:17.180 --> 00:32:25.139
making yourself so important that you place yourself above anything and everything else.

00:32:25.139 --> 00:32:34.260
You say, well, that's not really a sin. Go ask God if that's a sin. Go ask God if the

00:32:34.260 --> 00:32:40.180
pride and the self-will and selfishness. Ask God if he's pretty concerned about that. Stop

00:32:40.180 --> 00:32:51.860
excusing it. Rebellion against parents. Well, it's just the normal stage. I'm this age. Stop.

00:32:51.860 --> 00:32:58.620
It's not okay with God. God's first promise to a child was that he would obey and honor

00:32:58.620 --> 00:33:07.419
his parents. He made promises about that. That's not a little thing to God. You say,

00:33:07.460 --> 00:33:11.900
well, I don't voice it. Well, do you have it in your heart? That's where we're talking about it

00:33:11.900 --> 00:33:24.100
being. Like a sack of submission from a wife. Well, my husband, he's just—stop. God's not

00:33:24.100 --> 00:33:32.340
okay with that. Well, as a husband, he doesn't love her like Christ loved the church, but I mean,

00:33:32.340 --> 00:33:40.980
he does provide. Stop it. Our responsibility to our wives does not stop with a paycheck,

00:33:40.980 --> 00:33:47.260
for goodness sake. We are to love them and treat them like Christ loved the church,

00:33:47.260 --> 00:33:56.020
and sir, you may not excuse yourself out of that. I'm just telling you it's those little

00:33:56.020 --> 00:34:02.380
things. Oh, preacher, I don't smoke. I don't drink. I don't even chew tobacco. I made it.

00:34:02.380 --> 00:34:08.900
I'm a good Christian. Hey, long ago when I got saved, I did all—I didn't chew tobacco. I did

00:34:08.900 --> 00:34:14.900
the rest of those things, and I was so proud of myself when I stopped cussing, and stopped drinking,

00:34:14.900 --> 00:34:19.660
and stopped smoking. I thought, man, I've arrived. And then God said to me, now we're just starting

00:34:19.660 --> 00:34:27.380
on the hard stuff. And now I've been saved since 1975, and you know what? We are down to the hard

00:34:27.380 --> 00:34:37.860
stuff. And I've got stuff that I want to accept. I say, look how much I've served you. Look how

00:34:37.860 --> 00:34:42.540
much I've tried to help others. Look at how much I've studied. Look at how much—preacher, God,

00:34:42.540 --> 00:34:48.220
you just ought to leave me alone on this. And God says, no. No, we're on a journey here, Doc,

00:34:48.220 --> 00:35:01.779
and it's not okay to leave it lay in your heart. No love for the lost. I know people that go to

00:35:01.779 --> 00:35:08.420
church all of their lives and never one time genuinely care to try to tell somebody that's

00:35:08.540 --> 00:35:19.339
lost that Jesus can save them. Hurt feelings. Prejudice. Prejudice. I was born and raised

00:35:19.339 --> 00:35:29.339
up for Kentucky. That stuff has just acted like it's normal. It's not normal. It's not right.

00:35:29.339 --> 00:35:43.020
Not generous. Not a tither. Not a giver. Not a sharer. You say, you done, preacher? I am done.

00:35:43.020 --> 00:35:55.820
But I'm saying this. It really comes down to the hard stuff. It comes down to where God says to me,

00:35:55.980 --> 00:36:09.540
hey, I see that. And that's a limiting factor in your life. And I'm not calling us horrible people.

00:36:09.540 --> 00:36:16.580
I'm not. I'm saying to you at the beginning, I think we're the cream of the crop. And I wouldn't

00:36:16.580 --> 00:36:20.779
preach it to people that weren't the cream of the crop because the rest, a lot of folks could care

00:36:20.779 --> 00:36:25.779
less if they get any better. They could care less if they go any deeper. They care less if they

00:36:25.779 --> 00:36:30.580
grow. But you and I, we've got to come to the place where we say, God, okay, we're down to the

00:36:30.580 --> 00:36:38.660
hard stuff. Will you help me? And Lord, I'm confessing to you that that is in my life. That

00:36:38.660 --> 00:36:42.739
that little thing that I like to excuse, that thing that the rest of the world would say,

00:36:42.739 --> 00:36:49.500
that's not sin. That thing that is laying there and in there and there's so difficult for me to

00:36:49.700 --> 00:36:57.779
deal with. God, would you help me? I don't want to limit my life in prayer. I don't want to know

00:36:57.779 --> 00:37:03.940
it's there and claim to be consistent with everything you call godly. And I don't want

00:37:03.940 --> 00:37:12.459
to go through the motions. Lord, I want you to help me get this iniquity out of my heart. Now,

00:37:12.459 --> 00:37:18.700
let me end with this. Look at verse 19. But verily God hath heard me. You know what the

00:37:18.700 --> 00:37:25.619
psalmist is saying? I was in a bad way. I had some bad stuff going on in my life. I had stuff

00:37:25.619 --> 00:37:31.820
that I was approving. I had stuff that I was hiding. But God got a hold of my heart. I confessed it.

00:37:31.820 --> 00:37:39.179
I got it out of my heart. And God now hears me. God hath heard me. He hath attended to the voice

00:37:39.179 --> 00:37:48.059
of my prayer. Blessed be God which hath not turned away my prayer, get this, nor his mercy.

00:37:48.059 --> 00:38:01.619
Man, the greatest blessing we have is God's mercy and long-suffering. God is patient with us and

00:38:01.619 --> 00:38:08.660
brings us to moments and places in our life where we can re-engage and say, God, I know that is

00:38:08.660 --> 00:38:14.899
there. Will you help me with that? I don't want it to be limiting. And mercifully, not giving us

00:38:14.899 --> 00:38:22.660
what we deserve, God says, I'll help. I'll help you. The psalmist said, I've regarded iniquity in

00:38:22.660 --> 00:38:27.820
my heart. I know what it is for God not to hear me. I know what it is for God not to be moved

00:38:27.820 --> 00:38:34.860
when I need God to be moved. And I want that out of my life, but verily God hath heard me. Because

00:38:34.860 --> 00:38:46.780
his mercy in my life moved me to the point where with his help I could forsake that sin that I

00:38:46.780 --> 00:38:56.140
accepted as just who I am. Would you pray with me? Father, I pray that you'd speak to us tonight. I

00:38:57.099 --> 00:39:05.220
know the people in this room love you. I know the people in this room want revival in their

00:39:05.220 --> 00:39:13.640
own lives, in their own homes, in their church, and in this country. But I also know that we can

00:39:13.640 --> 00:39:22.900
be so limiting because we accept things that aren't the big sins as acceptable in our life.

00:39:22.900 --> 00:39:37.500
And Lord, if we truly want revival, if we really want to be in communication, to be led of the

00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:47.299
Spirit, to be used in a great way in any way, it will only be when we stop allowing sin to stay,

00:39:47.460 --> 00:39:58.299
stop approving sin as ours, stop accepting it's just a little one, and allow you to deal with us

00:39:58.299 --> 00:40:02.859
and help it be removed from our lives. It's a process. It's hard. It's not a

00:40:02.859 --> 00:40:09.919
an easy thing. We'll start and fail but God we will stop accepting it. We may start on

00:40:09.919 --> 00:40:17.659
getting it out and forsaking it. We may fail but we will stop accepting it. And oh God

00:40:17.659 --> 00:40:23.879
when we try and when we try to forsake and when we confess and when we work at it, you

00:40:23.879 --> 00:40:31.759
and your mercy will hear us. So Lord I pray for believers. I don't think anyone in here

00:40:31.759 --> 00:40:39.999
is an adulterer or a drunkard or a murderer but I do think there's people like me that

00:40:39.999 --> 00:40:46.799
have stuff that's hard to get out and we hold on to it. Because it's so hard we start to

00:40:46.799 --> 00:40:56.759
accept it not realizing how limiting it is. So Father you work. These people love you

00:40:56.759 --> 00:41:04.879
and you love them. You work in the way you want. I pray you do it. In Jesus name. Amen.

00:41:04.879 --> 00:41:10.199
As you stand our heads are bowed, our eyes are closed. I know this is a hard, hard invitation.

00:41:10.199 --> 00:41:15.519
I know nobody wants somebody to think we're coming down for something evil. Don't worry

00:41:15.519 --> 00:41:23.839
about what somebody thinks. Whatever is limiting deal with God about it and God will help you.

00:41:23.839 --> 00:41:30.759
Did you come as the piano plays? God there are some things. Oh they're not sin in the

00:41:30.759 --> 00:41:38.359
way the world sees sin. They're not big sin. But boy I know they're limiting. I know that

00:41:38.359 --> 00:41:43.679
you're not pleased with them being there. And I don't want to hold on to them anymore.

00:41:43.679 --> 00:41:48.919
God I may start and I may fail but I'm going to start. I don't want to be accepting of

00:41:48.919 --> 00:41:56.919
them anymore. I'm just asking you Lord I'm real with you. It's tough. It's there. I'm

00:41:56.919 --> 00:42:04.199
asking you will you help me empty those things from my heart. If a man regards iniquity in

00:42:04.199 --> 00:42:15.359
his heart the Lord will not hear him. He won't be moved. Thank God. God hath heard my prayer.

00:42:15.359 --> 00:42:23.439
It's God's mercy and long-suffering and spirit will help us get where we need to be. God help us.

